    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-12-31T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-12-31T14:00:00-05:00" n="486"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.113 Tobacco Products/49: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-12-31T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 31, 1934—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>401. Your 605, December 30, 10 a.m.,<note n="37" xml:id="d486fn37">Not
                        printed.</note> in regard to proposed increase in the import duties
                    applicable to leaf tobacco.</p>
                <p>If on further investigation the report outlined in your telegram under reference
                    proves to be correct, it is assumed that Legation will bear in mind and act in
                    accordance with the views and suggestions of the Department as indicated in its
                    telegram No. 316 of October 2, 1 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
